            "abstract": {
                "p": "The invention relates to a household solar energy and hydrogen energy system in the technical field of energy, comprising a solar thermal collector, a high-temperature water tank, a normal-temperature water tank, a reaction bed, a solar energy hydrogen generator, a cooling tower and a hydrogen storage tank. The high-temperature output ends of the solar thermal collector, the high-temperature water tank and the reaction bed are sequentially connected in series to form a high-temperature loop; the normal-temperature input ends of the normal-temperature water tank, the cooling tower and the reaction bed are sequentially connected in series to form a low-temperature loop; the output ends of the solar energy hydrogen generator are sequentially connected in series with the hydrogen storage tank and the reaction bed; and the high-temperature loop is isolated from the low-temperature loop. In the invention, the low-pressure hydrogen generated by the solar energy hydrogen generator can be converted into high-pressure hydrogen and encapsulated in a high-pressure tank. The whole device has simple structure, lower cost and stable operation. The hydrogen can be stored and used more conveniently with independent production, thereby realizing self feed of household energy and providing gas source for utilization of the hydrogen energy."
